  notes:
    - "Wave 672 (st3376): __trunc__, __round__, __index__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __trunc__/__round__/__index__ dict-presence (math.trunc(x), round(x), operator.index(x))."
    - "All values False — UUID, Struct, and socket types have no truncation, rounding, or integer-conversion protocol."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __trunc__, __round__, or __index__ in its __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not support math.trunc(x), round(x), or operator.index(x)."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no truncation, rounding, or integer-conversion protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

